The Democratic Republic of Congo’s MD Services SARL has in a very short space of time established itself as a leading staff recruitment and human resources (HR) management specialist across the country. Laura Cornish had the opportunity to sit down with M. Mudogo Rainizana Didi at this year’s DRC Mining Week conference and exhibition to talk about the company’s achievements, capabilities and growth strategy moving forward. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 8 2018. It will be published online on the 14th September 2018. You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy